This was one of the creatures that got me back on the idea of [Recurring Nightmare](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Recurring Nightmare). Run two of them and cycle back and forth. Especially fun if you happen to get [Gisela, Blade of Goldnight](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Gisela, Blade of Goldnight). Eliminate an entire group in multi-player in one swoop. Ba-BOOM!   

@DarthParallax; It's weird; I would never think to play him like that. I'm putting him in my deck TOO combo him in multi-player; On top of my above comment is a [Living Death](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Living Death) with 2 of him in the graveyard and Gisela. As they have to come into play for the legend rule to apply, Gisela would also be in play; therefore when they both die due to legend ruling each one will deal 10 damage to each of my opponents; if no one has gained life that's game. Possibly by turn 3...can't wait.  

I'm not criticising you; I do see some appeal in leaving him there as a threat. No one want's to kill him, which is always fun...then again I have friends who play with [Swords](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Swords ) ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)
